  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - ENCHANTER</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>20-25+ KILL SARANKS IN LAKE OF ILL OMEN</font> - <small>Fenadyen of Bertoxxolus, Bertoxxulous</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>First off you need to have Kunark to do this.<br>
From levels 20-25 I gained at least a bubble an hour here<br>
even with level 28-30 members in my group. So don't worry about<br>
the levels of the group too much. Higher level groups mean you
will<br>
be safer. At level 20-22 or so you mainly will play buffer and <br>
mana provider, which while a little boring still means you get to
rake in<br>
the XP for very little effort. By 22 or 23 you should have very
few resists so<br>
you can really start playing the role of mezer as well.<br>
<br>
Once you get Kunark head out to the Lake of Ill Omen,<br>
and start shouting Level XX Enchanter looking for Sarnak group<br>
Go to the fortress which is in the SW corner of the zone, and
start<br>
asking around too.<br>
<br>
Once you get into a group it becomes really easy to get XP. <br>
<br>
Once in the group, don't use your DD's. Save your mana for the<br>
occasional swarm and for beguile/alacrity. DD's just piss of the
sarnaks<br>
and suck up your mana way to fast.<br>
<br>
BTW remember to echo this mantra often: Everyone please /assist
the puller<br>
If you have a good group you won't have to say it often. If you
have a bad<br>
group they usually learn after the first swarm. If not ditch
them.<br>
<br>
From here, med the whole time except when the puller has some
incoming.<br>
If you are at the platform, sit near the edge where you have a
good view<br>
of the entrance to the inside. This way you can see a group of
mobs and<br>
mez one or all before the get to your group, that way there's
less a chance <br>
that someone will break your mez.<br>
<br>
Another great place and its not hard to hold is the 'Alcove'
which is<br>
in side. Here sit in the hall way so you can get a head start
again<br>
on the incomings and use mez as needed.<br>
<br>
Once you hit 24, Tanks LOVE alacrity. Its like clarity is for
casters.<br>
Save your mana for this. Its provides much more damage/mana than<br>
your dot or DD. And your tanks will remember you and even start
looking<br>
out for you.<br>
<br>
Also remeber if more than one comes use group mez, then if one<br>
breaks early and agros you, use color shift/flux to stun then
cast<br>
entrall immediately. This will then freeze one for even more
time.<br>
Plus its a way to get the mob away from where people might hit<br>
it and break your mez. Once you master this you may find yourself<br>
asking people not to save you from that one agro-ing. <br>
<br>
I hope this helps a bit. Its done wonders for me. Until this time<br>
I never really grouped, and never really used my mez spells.<br>
No I love doing both. Mez is so much more fun than just DD'ing.<br>
It gives you control over the life and death of your group.<br>
</p>

		</td></tr>
